<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Novig Maker — Line-Setting Edges</title>
<link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 100 100'><text y='.9em' font-size='90'>🎯</text></svg>">
<style>
:root {
  --bg: #0d1117; --surface: #161b22; --surface2: #1c2128; --border: #21262d;
  --text: #c9d1d9; --muted: #8b949e; --accent: #58a6ff;
  --green: #3fb950; --yellow: #d29922; --red: #f85149; --purple: #bc8cff;
  --sans: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Inter, ui-sans-serif, sans-serif;
  --mono: ui-monospace, "SF Mono", Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
}
* { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
body { background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); font-family: var(--sans);
  font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; padding: 1rem 1.25rem; }
a { color: var(--accent); }
header { margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.75rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
h1 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
h2 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
.meta-chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.4rem; }
.chip { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 0.1em 0.65em;
  font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--muted); }
.legend { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0.5rem 0 0.25rem;
  background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 0.6rem 0.8rem; }
.legend b { color: var(--text); }
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 12.5px; }
th, td { text-align: left; padding: 0.4rem 0.6rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); white-space: nowrap; }
th { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.03em; position: sticky; top: 0; background: var(--bg); }
tbody tr:hover { background: var(--surface); }
.mono { font-family: var(--mono); }
.pos { color: var(--green); font-weight: 600; }
.neg { color: var(--red); }
.muted { color: var(--muted); }
.tag { font-size: 0.68rem; padding: 0.05em 0.5em; border-radius: 10px; font-weight: 600; }
.tag-take { background: rgba(63,185,80,0.15); color: var(--green); border: 1px solid rgba(63,185,80,0.3); }
.tag-make { background: rgba(188,140,255,0.15); color: var(--purple); border: 1px solid rgba(188,140,255,0.3); }
.tag-mkt { background: var(--surface2); color: var(--muted); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
.count { color: var(--muted); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.8rem; }
details { margin-top: 1rem; }
summary { cursor: pointer; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.85rem; }
.empty { color: var(--muted); font-style: italic; padding: 0.5rem 0; }
/* ── Click-to-expand book breakdown ─────────────────────────────── */
.edge-row { cursor: pointer; }
.caret { color: var(--muted); display: inline-block; width: 0.9em; font-size: 0.7rem;
  transition: transform 0.1s; }
.edge-row.open .caret { transform: rotate(90deg); }
.src-badge { font-size: 0.62rem; padding: 0.04em 0.45em; border-radius: 8px;
  margin-left: 0.45em; border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--muted);
  vertical-align: middle; }
.src-1 { color: var(--yellow); border-color: rgba(210,153,34,0.4); background: rgba(210,153,34,0.12); }
.detail-row > td { background: var(--surface2); padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem 0.7rem 2rem; }
.detail-title { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.68rem; text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }
.detail-table { width: auto; }
.detail-table th, .detail-table td { border: none; padding: 0.12rem 1.6rem 0.12rem 0; }
.detail-table th { font-size: 0.64rem; }
.detail-novig { color: var(--muted); margin-top: 0.45rem; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <h1>🎯 Novig Maker — Line-Setting Edges (MLB)</h1>
  <div class="meta-chips">
    <span class="chip">Generated {{ generated_at }}</span>
    <span class="chip">Sharp fair: {{ sharp_labels | join(" + ") }} (devigged blend)</span>
    <span class="chip">TAKE ≥ {{ thresholds.take_min_edge_pct }}%</span>
    <span class="chip">MAKE ≥ {{ thresholds.make_min_edge_pct }}%</span>
    {% if thresholds.make_max_book_gap_pct %}<span class="chip">MAKE gap cap {{ thresholds.make_max_book_gap_pct }}%</span>{% endif %}
  </div>
</header>

<div class="legend">
  <b>TAKE</b> — Novig already pays <i>longer</i> than sharp fair, so backing it now is +EV. <b>EV%</b> is your edge.<br>
  <b>MAKE</b> — Novig's price is short of fair. <b>Post</b> a new best-in-market order at the suggested price (it clears the <b>+EV floor</b> = sharp fair, so it stays profitable) and let soft money on the other side fill it. <b>Gap</b> = how far Novig's current best sits below fair (your shading room). Posting <i>below</i> the floor beats the book but is &minus;EV — don't.<br>
  <span class="muted">Click any row to see which sharp books fed the fair value. A <span class="src-badge src-1">1&nbsp;bk</span> badge means only one book priced that side — treat it as less reliable.</span>
</div>

{% macro fair_detail_row(r, colspan) %}
<tr class="detail-row" hidden>
  <td colspan="{{ colspan }}">
    <div class="detail-title">Sharp books behind this fair value ({{ r.fair_book_count }})</div>
    <table class="detail-table">
      <tr><th>Book</th><th>Its line (this side)</th><th>Devigged fair</th></tr>
      {% for d in r.fair_details %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ book_labels.get(d.book, d.book) }}</td>
        <td class="mono">{{ d.raw_american }}</td>
        <td class="mono">{{ d.fair_american }} <span class="muted">({{ '%.1f' % (d.fair_prob * 100) }}%)</span></td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </table>
    <div class="detail-novig">
      Blended fair <span class="mono">{{ r.fair_american }}</span> ({{ r.fair_prob_pct }}%) ·
      Novig now <span class="mono">{{ r.novig_american }}</span> this side{% if r.novig_opp_american %} · <span class="mono">{{ r.novig_opp_american }}</span> opposite{% endif %}
    </div>
  </td>
</tr>
{% endmacro %}

<h2>✅ TAKE <span class="count">{{ take|length }} edge{{ '' if take|length == 1 else 's' }}</span></h2>
{% if take %}
<table>
<thead><tr>
  <th>Game</th><th>Start</th><th>Mkt</th><th>Side</th>
  <th>Sharp fair</th><th>Novig now</th><th>EV%</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for r in take %}
<tr class="edge-row" onclick="toggleDetail(this)">
  <td><span class="caret">▸</span>{{ r.game }}</td>
  <td class="muted">{{ r.commence_time | to_et }}</td>
  <td><span class="tag tag-mkt">{{ r.market }}</span></td>
  <td>{{ r.side }}</td>
  <td class="mono">{{ r.fair_american }} <span class="muted">({{ r.fair_prob_pct }}%)</span><span class="src-badge {{ 'src-1' if r.fair_book_count == 1 else '' }}">{{ r.fair_book_count }} bk</span></td>
  <td class="mono">{{ r.novig_american }}</td>
  <td class="pos">+{{ '%.1f' % r.take_ev_pct }}%</td>
</tr>
{{ fair_detail_row(r, 7) }}
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
{% else %}<div class="empty">No qualifying TAKE edges right now.</div>{% endif %}

<h2>🛠️ MAKE <span class="count">{{ make|length }} edge{{ '' if make|length == 1 else 's' }}</span></h2>
{% if make %}
<table>
<thead><tr>
  <th>Game</th><th>Start</th><th>Mkt</th><th>Side</th>
  <th>Sharp fair</th><th>Novig now</th><th>+EV floor</th><th>Post @</th><th>Gap</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
{% for r in make %}
<tr class="edge-row" onclick="toggleDetail(this)">
  <td><span class="caret">▸</span>{{ r.game }}</td>
  <td class="muted">{{ r.commence_time | to_et }}</td>
  <td><span class="tag tag-mkt">{{ r.market }}</span></td>
  <td>{{ r.side }}</td>
  <td class="mono">{{ r.fair_american }} <span class="muted">({{ r.fair_prob_pct }}%)</span><span class="src-badge {{ 'src-1' if r.fair_book_count == 1 else '' }}">{{ r.fair_book_count }} bk</span></td>
  <td class="mono muted">{{ r.novig_american }}</td>
  <td class="mono">{{ r.post_floor_american }}</td>
  <td class="mono pos">{{ r.post_american }} <span class="muted">(+{{ '%.1f' % r.make_ev_pct }}%)</span></td>
  <td>{{ '%.1f' % r.book_gap_pct }}%</td>
</tr>
{{ fair_detail_row(r, 9) }}
{% endfor %}
</tbody>
</table>
{% else %}<div class="empty">No qualifying MAKE edges right now.</div>{% endif %}

{% if other %}
<details>
  <summary>Below threshold ({{ other|length }})</summary>
  <table style="margin-top:0.5rem">
  <thead><tr><th>Game</th><th>Mkt</th><th>Side</th><th>Kind</th><th>Sharp fair</th><th>Novig now</th><th>Why hidden</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for r in other %}
  <tr>
    <td>{{ r.game }}</td>
    <td><span class="tag tag-mkt">{{ r.market }}</span></td>
    <td>{{ r.side }}</td>
    <td><span class="tag tag-{{ r.kind|lower }}">{{ r.kind }}</span></td>
    <td class="mono">{{ r.fair_american }}</td>
    <td class="mono">{{ r.novig_american }}</td>
    <td class="muted">{{ r.disqualify_reasons | join("; ") }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
  </table>
</details>
{% endif %}

<script>
function toggleDetail(row) {
  row.classList.toggle('open');
  const d = row.nextElementSibling;
  if (d && d.classList.contains('detail-row')) d.hidden = !d.hidden;
}
</script>
</body>
</html>
